    {
      "id": "1944750c-f3ba-80c7-98fb-e3b993629e84",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Most KT models use CFA, a binary problem (the answer is correct or incorrect), which limits the possible applications for KT models. Thus, the authors propose a set of Bayesian KT Models (FBKT and T2FBKT) to address continuous score scenarios. The results show that KT can go beyond regular applications with this approach.",
      "raw": {
        "object": "block",
